# 8. 枕の下に大きな夢を

Tsukasa: Here's to our successful New Year's performances...! Cheers!
Emu, Rui & Nene: Cheers! Cheers.
Rui: Robo-Nene, Lion Dance Robot, here's some fresh oil. I know it was a tough schedule, so thank you both for persevering.
KAITO: I was amazed to hear that, aside from the Wonder Stage, you were able to put on shows in 4 other places.
MEIKO: Me too! That's what I call a dynamic plan!
Len: Still, are you guys okay? Don't you feel tired at all?
Nene: To be honest, I wasn't sure we'd make it through when I first heard about what we'd be doing...
Nene: But I think we were able to pull it off because it ended up being more fun than expected.
Emu: Yeah! The guests at the Wonder Stage also really loved it—
Emu: Oh nooo!
Luka: Hm? Is something wrong, Emu?
Emu: What do I do?! I slept so well yesterday that I didn't have my first dream!
Rin: Your first dream...? Oh, of the new year?
Rui: If that's the case, won't the dream you see tonight count as your first for this year?
Emu: Wait, that counts?! Then, I'm gonna have a super wonderhoy dream tonight!
Nene: A wonderhoy dream... What does that entail?
Emu: Huh? Uhh, soo... You guys are all gonna be in it, including Miku and everyone...
Emu: And we'll put on lots and lots of shows in all sorts of different places like yesterday♪
Rui: Hehe. It's very similar to what we just experienced in real life, but it sounds like a wonderful first dream...
Miku: Yeah! I wanna see that dream too!
Emu: Then, let's draw it together! I heard that if you draw what you want to dream and put it under your pillow, you'll actually see it when you sleep!
Rin: Really? That sounds like fun♪
MEIKO: What if we got a big sheet of paper for that?! We could all draw on it and sleep on it afterward!
Luka: Oh, that means we'll all get to see the same dream♪ Where can we find a sheet of paper like that?
Emu: I'll help you guys look for one! Nene, let's go!
Nene: Huh? W-Wait...! You don't need to pull me!
KAITO: Haha. I guess we'll be sleeping directly on top of it instead of putting it under a pillow.
Rui: That'll be very interesting to see.
Miku: Huh...?
Miku: Is everything okay, Tsukasa? You're usually all wound up and ready to go in these situations.
Tsukasa: No, I'm fine... I was just reminiscing over what happened yesterday.
Miku: Yesterday?
Tsukasa: Yes. Asking for volunteers from the audience ended up being an interesting learning experience...
Tsukasa: (Ichika and the others sang in a way that felt so encouraging. That sort of singing performance is sure to invigorate any audience she sings for.)
Tsukasa: (Hanasato and her group also put on a wonderful performance. Based on how well they interacted with that audience, their shows must be out of this world...)
Tsukasa: (I can't forget Shiraishi and her teammate! I was so moved by the way they sang with so much passion! They certainly know how to please an audience.)
Tsukasa: (And...)
Tsukasa: (That girl... Yoisaki, was it? I was completely staggered by how she was able to come up with such a beautiful song on the spot.)
Tsukasa: (A show requires more than just actors. Everyone, including those involved with sound production, must work together to bring it to life.)
Tsukasa: (Moving forward, I'd like to work more on understanding what kind of music would suit certain scenes better.)
Tsukasa: So, I have quite a bit to work on in the future...!
Tsukasa: But it was a wonderful learning experience!
Miku: It was?! Then, I'm glad☆
Tsukasa: (It was as I suspected...)
Tsukasa: (I was able to make these realizations because I performed with different people at places we normally don't.)
Tsukasa: (Which means I can't let things just be...)
Tsukasa: (Something on the order of our ambassadorial performances may not be possible, but I need to start by asking to perform elsewhere.)
Tsukasa: (However, this is not something I can decide on my own. I'll need to speak with Emu's brothers first.)
Tsukasa: Yes...! I must do this! For the sake of my dream!
Emu: Everyone! We found a giant sheet of paper!
MEIKO: Let's all draw on it and have ourselves a little nap!
Rin: Yeah, let's draw♪ Oh, but what?
Lion Dance Robot: CHOMP CHOMP CHOMP!
Rin: Huh? You wanna draw too?
Lion Dance Robot: CHOMP!
Robo-Nene: Having put on a series of successful shows, he seems to be rather motivated.
Tsukasa: Ah, I see...! That's great to hear!
Tsukasa: Lion Dance Robot, let us keep putting on wonderful shows together moving forward!
Lion Dance Robot: CHOMP...! CHOMP...
Robo-Nene: Hm...?
Lion Dance Robot: CHOMP CHOMP... CHOMP CHOMP...!
Robo-Nene: He appears to be very excited. So excited that he may overheat soon...
Rui: Ah, which means he may once again...
Tsukasa: What?! That can only mean...
Lion Dance Robot: CHOMP!!!
Tsukasa: Nooo! He's coming after me again!
Emu: Oh no! Is Tsukasa gonna be okay?!
Rui: Hmm... He's designed to operate on his own, but it's interesting how he always chases after Tsukasa... I'll need to take a closer look at some point...
Rin: Haha! He does look excited! Let's play a game of tag before we draw♪
Tsukasa: Now is not the time for that!
Nene: Uhh, Rui...? Shouldn't you do something?
Rui: Hehe. I know. We wouldn't want our valiant troupe leader to get hurt. Emu, would you mind lending me a hand?
Emu: Okay! Let's go save Tsukasa together!
KAITO: Hehe... I see another fun and exciting year in the works.
Miku: Yup☆ I can't wait to see what happens!
